  "prompt": "How do I log in my Facebook account if you forgot your password?",
  "response": "If you've forgotten your Facebook password, you can reset it by following these steps:\n\n1. **Go to the Facebook login page**: Open your web browser and navigate to `www.facebook.com`.\n\n2. **Click on \"Forgot Password?\"**: Below the login fields, you'll see a link that says \"Forgot Password?\". Click on it.\n\n3. **Enter your email, phone number, or username**: A new page will open asking you to enter the email address, phone number, or username associated with your account. Type in the information and click \"Search\".\n\n4. **Verify your identity**: Facebook will try to find your account. Once found, you'll be asked to verify your identity. You can do this through several methods:\n   - **Email**: If you choose this option, Facebook will send a 6-digit code to the email address associated with your account. Check your email, enter the code on the Facebook page, and click \"Continue\".\n   - **Phone number**: If you select this option, a 6-digit code will be sent to your phone via SMS. Enter the code on the Facebook page and click \"Continue\".\n   - **Security questions**: If you've set up security questions, you may be asked to answer them. Provide the correct answers and click \"Continue\".\n\n5. **Reset your password**: After verifying your identity, you'll be prompted to enter a new password. Type in your new password, confirm it, and click \"Continue\".\n\n6. **Log in with your new password**: Return to the Facebook login page and enter your email or phone number and the new password to access your account.\n\nIf you're still having trouble, you can visit the Facebook Help Center or contact their support team for further assistance.",
